logy, health care for the global poor, and international public health policy, providing a broad overview of his work. It illuminates the depth and impact of Farmer’s contributions and demonstrates how, over time, this unassuming and dedicated doctor has fundamentally changed the way we think about health, international aid, and social justice.A portion of the proceeds from the sale of this book will be donated to Partners In Health.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEpidemiology. 0aMedical anthropology. 0aPoorxMedical care. 0aPoverty. 0aPublic health. 0aSocial justice. 0aSocial medicine. 7aMEDICAL / General.2bisacsh1 aCampos, Nicole Gastineau, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFarmer, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKeshavjee, Salmaan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKidder, Tracy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKim, Jim Yong, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKoenig, Serena P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLambert, Wesler, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLéandre, Fernet, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMukherjee, Joia S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNizeye, Bruce, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSaussy, Haun, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSaussy, Haun, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aStulac, Sara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWalton, David A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook p